==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proteose
<hw>Pro"te*ose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Prote</ets>id + <ets>-ose</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>One of a class of soluble products formed in the
digestion of proteids with gastric and pancreatic juice, and also by the
hydrolytic action of boiling dilute acids on proteids. Proteoses are
divided into the two groups, the <xex>primary</xex> and
<xex>secondary</xex> proteoses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proterandrous</ent>⟦br⟧
